Package io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.objectModel

Class MsdxObject

java.lang.Object
io.github.JeremyBloom.mosdex2.objectModel.MsdxObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
MsdxFile, MsdxInstance, MsdxModule, MsdxQuery, MsdxSchema, MsdxTable
public class MsdxObject
extends java.lang.Object
The base class for all MOSDEX objects. MOSDEX objects in general are represented as nodes of the Jackson Tree Model, and are accessed by calls to JsonNode methods, usually as get(fieldName) or as the iterators fields and elements.

However, certain objects also create Java objects. These fields (module, table, schema, query, instance, etc.) require special handling to create the corresponding objects. In particular, instance data is held in dataframes, because the node representation would be too cumbersome.

The objects represented by Java classes provide alternative access to certain fields of their parent objects.

The static member class Factory provides methods to read and write MOSDEX JSON.

    • toString

      public java.lang.String toString()
      Creates a simple string representation of the JSON representation of this object. It has no indentation or pretty printing, and instances show as a single representative record. To create a pretty JSON string, use one of the write methods of the factory or one of the class-specific show methods.
